    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1971-08-04T10:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1971-08-04T10:45:00-05:00" n="234"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                <head>234. Telegram 3312 From the <gloss type="from">Mission in Geneva</gloss> to
                    the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d234fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1970–1973, DEF 18–3 Switz
                        (GE). Confidential; Immediate. It was repeated to USNATO, Moscow, <gloss
                            target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>, USDel <gloss target="#t_SALT1"
                            >SALT</gloss> V, London, The Hague, Ottawa, Paris, Rome, and
                        Tokyo.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d234fn2">The telegram reported that the U.S.
                        and Soviet Co-Chairmen had reached agreement on the text of the draft
                        Biological Weapons Convention.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1971-08-04T15:45:00+00:00">August 4, 1971, 1545Z</date>
                </dateline>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subj:</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_CCD1">CCD</gloss> Co-Chairmen Meeting re Tabling of Draft
                            <gloss target="#t_BW1">BW</gloss> Convention</item>
                </list>
                <list type="references">
                    <head>Ref:</head>
                    <item>(A) State 137470; (B) USNATO 3217</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Begin summary: <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss> and Soviet Co-Chairmen
                        reached agreement August 4 on text of draft convention prohibiting
                        development, production and stockpiling of biological weapons (<gloss
                            target="#t_BW1">BW</gloss>) and on procedures for tabling this draft at
                            <gloss target="#t_CCD1">CCD</gloss> plenary August 5. End
                        summary.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>At Co-Chairmen meeting Aug 4, requested by <gloss target="#t_US1"
                            >US</gloss> Del after receipt reftel B, <persName corresp="#p_LJF1"
                            >Leonard</persName> (<gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss>) informed
                            <persName corresp="#p_RAA4">Roshchin</persName> (<gloss
                            target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss>) that we were prepared to accept five
                        changes in <pb facs="d234-02" n="2" xml:id="d234-02"/> text of draft <gloss
                            target="#t_BW1">BW</gloss> convention proposed by Sovs July 21 with
                        deletion of article “the” before the word “resolutions” in preambular para
                        10 of English text (see para 6 reftel a). <persName corresp="#p_RAA4"
                            >Roshchin</persName> agreed to this modification.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LJF1">Leonard</persName> told <persName
                            corresp="#p_RAA4">Roshchin</persName> that while <gloss target="#t_US1"
                            >US</gloss> allies did not object to our tabling draft on which we had
                        agreed with Sovs, our allies might wish to suggest some amendments or
                        changes in this draft during discussions of it in the <gloss
                            target="#t_CCD1">CCD</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RAA4">Roshchin</persName> pointed out several minor,
                        non-substantive discrepancies in US and Russian text which <persName
                            corresp="#p_LJF1">Leonard</persName> agreed, at <persName
                            corresp="#p_RAA4">Roshchin</persName>’s request, to correct (these are
                        identified in septel containing full text). Co-Chairmen agreed that during
                        next stage in negotiations <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss> and Sovs would
                        further review English and Russian texts in order achieve best possible
                        accord in languages.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>On procedure, Co-Chairmen agreed to table identical but separate texts of
                        draft <gloss target="#t_BW1">BW</gloss> convention at <gloss
                            target="#t_CCD1">CCD</gloss> plenary meeting morning Aug 5. Sovs and
                        their allies will co-sponsor one text (<gloss target="#t_CCD1"
                        >CCD</gloss>/337) with original in Russian. <gloss target="#t_US1"
                            >US</gloss> will sponsor separate text (<gloss target="#t_CCD1"
                            >CCD</gloss>/338) with original in English. Co-Chairmen also agreed to
                        provide Non-aligned dels with advance copies afternoon Aug 1 (we have
                        provided <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss> allies morning Aug 4 with advance
                        copy of text that will be tabled).</item>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>Rimestad</signed>
                    </closer>
                </list>
            </div>
